result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin E Ginter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Homicide by Negligent Operation/Vehicle, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.10(1).
  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Austin E Ginter in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Defendant Austin E Ginter in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:16 AM. Bennett also has at counsel table his private investigator for the case. State and Bennett believe that 15CF82 was to be dismissed and read in. Bennett states his inaccuracies found in State's PSI. State notes no inaccuracies or corrections. State will have family members that would like to make statements today. Court prefers to hear from any parties that wish to make a statement today. State's first witness makes statement (9:24 AM). State's second witness makes statement (9:34 AM). State's third witness makes statement (9:39 AM). State's fourth witness makes statement (9:47 AM). State's fifth witness makes statement (9:55 AM). Witness provides Court with a set of 5 pictures of the vehicle involved in the incident. Court will mark all 5 as exhibit #1. Witness provides another picture of the incident - will be marked as exhibit #2. Witness provides another picture of the incident - will be marked as exhibit #3. Court receives all 7 pictures as one exhibit (#1) after no objections (10:08 AM). State makes Court aware of some pictures that it has submitted and asks that they be made part of the record and asks that they be sealed. Court will accept these additional submitted pictures and will mark them as exhibit #2 and will seal them upon conclusion of the sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - has complied with victim notification requirements. Bennett objects to a statement made by State - no ruling (10:23 AM). State continues with sentencing argument - recommends on each count - 10 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of extended supervision - consecutive to each other, restitution of $20,634.37 (includes VW surcharge). Recess at 10:28 AM. Back on record at 10:41 AM with same appearances. Bennett has witnesses that will be making statements as well. Defense's first witness makes statement (10:42 AM). Defense's second witness makes statement (10:48 AM). Defense's third witness makes statement (10:50 AM). Defense's fourth witness makes statement (10:53 AM). Defense's fifth witness makes statement (10:55 AM). Defense's sixth witness makes statement (11:01 AM). Defense's seventh witness makes statement (11:04 AM). Defendant makes statement and the letters he is reading off of will be admitted as evidence and marked as exhibit #3 (11:08 AM). Bennett makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends to withhold sentence and place on probation for 4 years with conditions of: 6-9 months in county jail on each count - concurrent to each other - credit of 184 days. State rebutts at 11:56 AM. Bennett objects - no ruling (11:58 AM). Defendant makes additonal statement, apologizes to victim's family. Victim's mother makes statement (12:00 PM). Court rejects probation and sentences the defendant to the following: count #4 - 10 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 5 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES; #6 - 8 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 5 years of ES - consecutive to count #4, conditions of ES include: adopt recommendation as stated in PSI, AODA and follow thru, mental health treatment, cognitive testing/program and any and all other conditions as deemed appropriate by P&P, submit DNA sample with surcharge, costs on each count, restitution as previously stated - paid with 25% of any prison funds/earnings, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, credit for 184 days, not eligible for any programs in prison, right to appeal.
